    "There is a widespread assumption that manipulation is antithetical to autonomy (Susser et al., 2019b), but that view has yet to be corroborated from an empirical perspective (Klenk & Hancock, 2019), and we already know that people's judgements about manipulation's impact are more nuanced (Osman & Bechlivanidis, 2021).",
    "We also know that generative AI can have an impact on people's moral judgements (Krügel et al., 2023), but it is unclear whether and why the influence in question qualifies as manipulation or not."
